-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Maple, Relapasa, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-17T21:12:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/peru-stocks-buenaventura-credicorp-rio-alto-mining.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a fifth session, dropping 1
percent to 20,643.88. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.2
percent to 2,642.44.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell for a fourth session,
losing 3.7 percent to $1.04 after crude declined to a six-month
low in New York, said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-based
brokerage Coril SAB.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, dropped 3.6 percent to 80 centimos, a
five-month low.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, rose
1.9 percent to $3.78 after gold rebounded in  New York .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, gained 0.7 percent to $36.05.  To contact the reporter on this story:
